track_notes:
2.4 mile hike along the Bartram Trail from Harrison Gap with 1270 EG (but also 700 EL). Hike is fairly difficult due to it consisting of 5 steep climbs and descents with only a few sections to catch your breath. The trailhead in Harrison Gap is located at the end of FS Road 713 which is open from 3/15-12/31.

Summit is just off of the trail with plenty of room for antennas.

Year round access is available at Wallace Branch (35.180, -83.433), approximately 3 miles east of Wilkes Knob on the Bartram Trail.
track_title: W4C/WM-102 Wilkes Knob from Harrison Gap - Seasonal Access
